text: Gas Accord II Settlement Participants :
label: compound compound nummod compound root punct

text: Attached is PG&E 's Gas Accord II ( GA II ) Settlement Proposal .
label: root aux nmod case compound compound nummod punct appos nummod punct compound nsubj punct

text: We believe it addresses many of the issues and concerns you have raised in the workshops .
label: nsubj root nsubj ccomp obj case det nmod cc conj nsubj aux acl case det obl punct

text: As an overview , this proposal : * Maintains the basic Gas Accord structure in place today for the period 2003 to 2007 . *
label: case det obl punct det nsubj punct punct root det amod compound compound obj case nmod nmod case det obl compound case nmod punct punct

text: * Offers end user transportation rates for 2003 lower for most customers than rates in effect today . *
label: punct root compound compound compound obj case nmod amod case amod obl case obl case nmod nmod punct punct

text: * Provides for vintaged Redwood path rates for core customers . *
label: punct root case amod compound compound obl case compound nmod punct punct

text: * Offers a 7.5 cent / dth rate to large customers while minimizing rate changes to other customers , minimizing the incentive for these customers to seek to bypass local transmission charges and other CPUC - approved charges . *
label: punct root det nummod compound case nmod obj case amod obl mark advcl compound obj case amod nmod punct advcl det obj mark det nsubj mark acl mark xcomp amod compound obj cc amod compound punct amod conj punct punct

text: * Adopts guidelines to improve reliability and help moderate prices in gas commodity markets , and identifies the capital projects needed to meet these guidelines over the course of the GA II period ( 2003 - 2007 ) . *
label: punct root obj mark acl obj cc conj xcomp obj case compound compound obl punct cc conj det compound obj acl mark advcl det obj case det obl case det compound nummod nmod punct appos case nmod punct punct punct

text: * Provides a high degree of rate stability , with a 3.5 % escalator to capture both inflation and the cost of needed capital projects .
label: punct root det amod obj case compound nmod punct case det nummod compound obl mark acl cc obj cc det conj case amod compound nmod punct

text: The guaranteed rates will be adjustable only for significant changes in the cost of capital or increased costs due to governmental requirements or catastrophic events . *
label: det amod nsubj aux cop root advmod case amod obl case det nmod case nmod cc amod conj case fixed amod nmod cc amod conj punct punct

text: * Preserves a rate differential between the Redwood and Baja paths , although somewhat less than the current differential . *
label: punct root det compound obj case det compound cc conj nmod punct mark advmod advcl case det amod obl punct punct

text: * Proposes a two - stage open season for firm transportation services beginning in 2003 , with end users receiving a first option on available capacity . *
label: punct root det nummod punct compound amod obj case compound compound nmod acl case obl punct mark compound nsubj acl det amod obj case amod nmod punct punct

text: * Maintains the core aggregation program with some adjustments .
label: punct root det compound compound obj case det nmod punct

text: PG&E also anticipates that the Core Procurement Incentive Mechanism ( CPIM ) will be similar to today 's mechanism , but will reflect the somewhat larger capacity holdings needed to meet anticipated increases in core demand and to meet a 1 - day in 10 - year cold weather event .
label: nsubj advmod root mark det compound compound compound nsubj punct appos punct aux cop ccomp case nmod case obl punct cc aux conj det advmod amod compound obj acl mark advcl amod obj case compound nmod cc mark conj det nummod punct compound case nummod punct nmod amod compound obj punct

text: This also will serve as a reminder that an all - Party meeting is scheduled at PG&E 's headquarters in San Francisco on January 10 and 11 , to discuss this proposal and to respond to your questions .
label: nsubj advmod aux root case det obl mark det det punct compound nsubj aux acl case nmod case obl case nmod flat case obl nummod cc conj punct mark advcl det obj cc mark conj case nmod obl punct

text: We look forward to answering your questions and receiving your feedback .
label: nsubj root advmod mark advcl nmod obj cc conj nmod obj punct

text: The attached documents include the GA II Settlement proposal , an Attachment ( a copy of PG&E 's proposed Gas Rule 27 ) , and a set of supporting workpapers .
label: det amod nsubj root det compound nummod compound obj punct det conj punct det appos case nmod case amod compound nmod nummod punct punct cc det conj case amod nmod punct

text: Finally , please note that the Settlement document and the Attachment are in " Word 2000 " format .
label: advmod punct discourse root mark det compound nsubj cc det conj cop case punct compound nummod punct ccomp punct

text: We would be glad to provide the same documents in an earlier version of Word , upon request by individual Parties .
label: nsubj aux cop root mark advcl det amod obj case det amod obl case nmod punct case obl case amod nmod punct

text: We look forward to seeing you on January 10 - 11 .
label: nsubj root advmod mark advcl obj case obl nummod case nmod punct

text: Probing the ' palace coup '
label: root det punct compound obj punct

text: Electricity : A panel focuses on price hikes and the actions of the ISO president .
label: root punct det nsubj parataxis case compound obl cc det conj case det compound nmod punct

text: September 26 , 2001
label: root nummod punct nummod

text: By KIMBERLY KINDY
label: case root flat

text: The Orange County Register
label: det amod compound root

text: SACRAMENTO
label: root

text: A state Senate committee is set today to start serving 16 subpoenas on electricity producers and officials who manage California 's energy grid to determine whether they acted in concert to manipulate energy prices .
label: det compound compound nsubj aux root obl mark xcomp xcomp nummod obj case compound obl cc conj nsubj acl nmod case compound obj mark advcl mark nsubj ccomp case obl mark advcl compound obj punct

text: The investigative committee , headed by state Sen. Joe Dunn , D - Santa Ana , is focusing on a series of events last fall filled with enough Shakespearean plot twists and intrigue that it has earned a name around the Capitol : " the palace coup . "
label: det amod nsubj punct acl case compound obl flat flat punct appos punct compound appos punct aux root case det obl case nmod amod nmod acl case amod amod compound obl cc conj mark nsubj aux acl det obj case det obl punct punct det compound parataxis punct punct

text: Lawmakers and consumer groups allege that the events - directed by the man who heads the state 's energy grid - fueled the California energy crisis , pushed the state into the power - buying business and helped make billions of dollars for power producers .
label: nsubj cc compound conj root mark det nsubj punct acl case det obl nsubj acl det nmod case compound obj punct ccomp det compound compound obj punct conj det obj case det compound punct compound obl cc conj xcomp obj case nmod case compound obl punct

text: The central question behind the palace coup is whether Terry Winter , the president of the Independent System Operator , acted alone when he took steps to remove key price caps designed to limit the amount power generators could charge .
label: det amod nsubj case det compound nmod cop mark nsubj flat punct det appos case det amod compound nmod punct root advmod advmod nsubj advcl obj mark acl amod compound obj acl mark advcl det obj compound nsubj aux acl punct

text: Winter defied his own board and Gov. Gray Davis when he filed a 50 - page request to remove the caps , records and interviews show .
label: nsubj ccomp nmod amod obj cc conj flat flat advmod nsubj advcl det nummod punct compound obj mark acl det obj punct nsubj cc conj root punct

text: " I do n't know how these events could have taken place without some concerted effort , " said Dunn .
label: punct nsubj aux advmod ccomp advmod det nsubj aux aux ccomp obj case det amod obl punct punct root nsubj punct

text: The subpoenas will force those involved , including Winter , to provide sworn testimony about the events to the committee , and to turn over e-mails , personal calendars and memos .
label: det nsubj aux root obj acl punct case nmod punct mark xcomp amod obj case det nmod case det obl punct cc mark conj compound obj punct amod conj cc conj punct

text: Davis spokesman Steve Maviglio said the governor felt " betrayed " by the actions of Winter .
label: compound flat nsubj flat root det nsubj ccomp punct xcomp punct case det obl case nmod punct

text: " The governor believes it was the defining moment , when what was a mounting problem turned into an instant crisis , " Maviglio said .
label: punct det nsubj ccomp nsubj cop det amod ccomp punct advmod nsubj cop det amod acl advcl case det amod obl punct punct nsubj root punct

text: Winter refused comment , referring all questions to the public relations office .
label: nsubj root obj punct advcl det obj case det amod compound obl punct

text: ISO spokesman Gregg Fishman said Dunn 's committee will find no criminal conduct .
label: compound compound nsubj flat root nmod case nsubj aux ccomp det amod obj punct

text: The decision was made by ISO upper management with one goal in mind : to keep the lights on .
label: det nsubj aux root case compound amod obl mark nummod nsubj case advcl punct mark appos det obj compound punct

text: At the time , generators were refusing to sell power in California because of the price caps .
label: case det obl punct nsubj aux root mark xcomp obj case obl case fixed det compound obl punct

text: " It was an emergency , " Fishman said .
label: punct nsubj cop det ccomp punct punct nsubj root punct

text: " We had to take action . ''
label: punct nsubj root mark xcomp obj punct punct

text: What became known as the palace coup began on Oct. 26 when ISO board members voted for severe restrictions on the amount of money electricity producers could charge for power .
label: nsubj csubj xcomp case det compound obl root case obl nummod advmod compound compound nsubj advcl case amod obl case det nmod case nmod compound nsubj aux acl case obl punct

text: The restrictions would drive prices as low as $ 65 per megawatt - nearly 12 times below the $ 750 per megawatt limits of seven months earlier .
label: det nsubj aux root obj advmod xcomp case obl nummod case nmod punct advmod compound nmod case det compound nummod case nmod nmod case nummod nmod advmod punct

text: " They ( electricity generators ) grinned and beared the $ 750 price cap , but this new plan by ISO was too much , " said Dunn , whose committee has been investigating since March .
label: punct nsubj punct compound appos punct ccomp cc conj det compound nummod compound obj punct cc det amod nsubj case nmod cop advmod conj punct punct root nsubj punct nmod nsubj aux aux acl case obl punct

text: " All hell broke loose . ''
label: punct det nsubj root advmod punct punct

text: Records show that on Oct. 31 , power generators and electricity traders filed letters with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission , demanding that the new plan be killed .
label: nsubj root mark case obl nummod punct compound nsubj cc compound conj ccomp obj case det amod compound amod obl punct advcl mark det amod nsubj aux ccomp punct

text: The letters , six in all , were sent within two hours of each other and represented dozens of power generators .
label: det nsubj punct appos case nmod punct aux root case nummod obl case nmod fixed cc conj obj case compound nmod punct

text: " If not removed immediately , the ( ISO ) price cap will sow confusion in the market , threaten reliability and stifle new investment in generating capacity , '' read one letter written by Duke Energy Vice President William Hall III .
label: punct mark advmod advcl advmod punct det punct compound punct compound nsubj aux ccomp obj case det obl punct conj obj cc conj amod obj case compound nmod punct punct root nummod nsubj acl case compound compound compound compound obl flat nummod punct

text: Although there is nothing illegal about the generators acting together to lobby against price caps , Dunn believes the letters and other actions around the same time showed clear coordination among energy officials .

text: China 's insatiable demand for energy is prompting fears of financial and diplomatic collisions around the globe as it seeks reliable supplies of oil from as far away as Brazil and Sudan .

label: amod compound nsubj case nmod aux root det amod obj case nmod

text: The connection , however , lies in an order issued last year by President Hu Jintao to seek secure oil supplies abroad - preferably ones which could not be stopped by America in case of conflict over Taiwan .

text: For the United States and Europe are far more concerned with the even more sensitive issues of China 's relations with " pariah states " .

text: But as its economy has expanded by an average of nine per cent per year for the last two decades , so has its demand for energy .

text: North Carolina Religious Coalition for Marriage Equality Declaration of Religious Leaders April 19 , 2004
label: compound compound amod compound case compound nmod root case amod nmod nmod nummod punct nummod

text: The most fundamental human right , after the necessities of food , clothing and shelter , is the right to affection and the supportive love of other human beings .
label: det advmod amod amod nsubj punct case det nmod case nmod punct conj cc conj punct cop det root case nmod cc det amod conj case amod amod nmod punct

text: We become most fully human when we love another person .
label: nsubj root advmod advmod xcomp advmod nsubj advcl det obj punct

text: We can grow in our capacity to be human - to be loving - in a family unit .
label: nsubj aux root case nmod obl mark cop acl punct mark cop parataxis punct case det compound obl punct

text: This right to love and form a family is so fundamental that our United States Constitution takes it for granted in its dedication to " secure the blessings of liberty to ourselves and our posterity . ‚Äù
label: det nsubj mark acl cc conj det obj cop advmod root mark nmod amod compound nsubj advcl obj mark advcl case nmod obl mark punct acl det obj case nmod case nmod cc nmod conj punct punct

text: The North Carolina Constitution likewise affirms the ‚Äú inalienable rights ‚Äù of human beings to " life , liberty , the enjoyment of the fruits of their own labor , and the pursuit of happiness . "
label: det compound compound nsubj advmod root det punct amod obj punct case amod nmod case punct nmod punct conj punct det conj case det nmod case nmod amod nmod punct cc det conj case nmod punct punct

text: Throughout history , tyrants have known that by denying the right of oppressed peoples to form and nurture families , they can kill the spirit of those peoples .
label: case obl punct nsubj aux root mark mark advcl det obj case amod nmod mark acl cc conj obj punct nsubj aux ccomp det obj case det nmod punct

text: > From the shameful history of slavery in America , the injustice of forbidding people to marry is evident as a denial of a basic human right .
label: punct case det amod obl case nmod case nmod punct det nsubj mark acl obj mark xcomp cop root case det obl case det amod amod nmod punct

text: The American laws forbidding interracial marriage , now struck down , were clearly discriminatory .
label: det amod nsubj acl amod obj punct advmod acl compound punct cop advmod root punct

text: Denial of the status of marriage to those who would freely accept its responsibilities creates legal and economic inequities and social injustice .
label: nsubj case det nmod case nmod case nmod nsubj aux advmod acl nmod obj root amod cc conj obj cc amod conj punct

text: We feel called to protest and oppose this injustice .
label: nsubj root xcomp mark advcl cc conj det obj punct

text: As religious people , clergy and lay leaders , we are mandated by faith to stand for justice in our common civic life .
label: case amod obl punct conj cc amod conj punct nsubj aux root case obl mark xcomp case obl case nmod amod amod obl punct

text: We oppose the use of sacred texts and religious traditions to deny legal equity to same - gender couples .
label: nsubj root det obj case amod nmod cc amod conj mark acl amod obj case amod punct compound obl punct

text: As concerned citizens we affirm the liberty of adults of the same gender to love and marry .
label: case amod obl nsubj root det obj case nmod case det amod nmod mark acl cc conj punct

text: We insist that no one , especially the state , is allowed to coerce people into marriage or bar two consenting adults , whether of the same or differing genders , from forming the family unit that lets them be more fully loving , thus more fully human .
label: nsubj root mark det nsubj punct advmod det appos punct aux ccomp mark xcomp obj case obl cc conj nummod amod obj punct mark case det acl cc amod conj punct mark advcl det compound obj nsubj acl obj cop advmod advmod xcomp punct advmod advmod advmod conj punct

text: We respect the fact that debate and discussion continue in many of our religious communities as to the scriptural , theological and liturgical issues involved .
label: nsubj root det obj mark nsubj cc conj acl case obl case nmod amod nmod case fixed det amod punct conj cc conj obl acl punct

text: However , we draw on our many faith traditions to arrive at a common conviction .
label: advmod punct nsubj root case nmod amod compound obl mark advcl case det amod obl punct

text: We are resolved that the State should not interfere with same - gender couples who choose to marry and share fully and equally in the rights , responsibilities , and commitments of civil marriage .
label: nsubj aux root mark det nsubj aux advmod ccomp case amod punct compound obl nsubj acl mark xcomp cc conj advmod cc conj case det obl punct conj punct cc conj case amod nmod punct

text: We affirm freedom of conscience in this matter .
label: nsubj root obj case nmod case det obl punct

text: We recognize that the state may not require religious groups to officiate at , or bless , same - gender marriages .
label: nsubj root mark det nsubj aux advmod ccomp amod obj mark xcomp case punct cc conj punct amod punct compound obl punct

text: Likewise , a denial of state civil recognition dishonors the religious convictions of those communities and clergy who officiate at , and bless , same - gender marriages .
label: advmod punct det nsubj case compound amod nmod root det amod obj case det nmod cc conj nsubj acl obl punct cc conj punct amod punct compound conj punct

text: The state may not favor the convictions of one religious group over another by denying individuals their fundamental right to marry and to have those marriages recognized by civil law .
label: det nsubj aux advmod root det obj case nummod amod nmod case obl mark advcl iobj nmod amod obj mark acl cc mark conj det obj xcomp case amod obl punct

text: As faith leaders , we commit ourselves to public action , visibility , education , and mutual support in the service of the right and freedom to marry .
label: case compound obl punct nsubj root obj case amod obl punct conj punct conj punct cc amod conj case det nmod case det nmod cc conj mark acl punct

text: The One Reason Why All Americans Should Oppose The Nomination Of Samuel Alito

text: He Would Tear Down Our System Of Checks And Balances , Giving Far Too Much Power To The President
label: nsubj aux root compound nmod obj case nmod cc conj punct advcl advmod advmod amod obj case det obl

text: My Fellow Americans :
label: nmod amod root punct

text: As many of you may have heard , President Bush has nominated a long - time Federal Judge named Samuel Alito to become the next member of the United States Supreme Court , to fill a vacancy created by the retirement of another member of the Court .
label: mark nsubj case nmod aux aux advcl punct nsubj flat aux root det amod punct compound amod obj acl xcomp flat mark advcl det amod xcomp case det amod compound amod nmod punct mark advcl det obj acl case det obl case det nmod case det nmod punct

text: Under our Constitution , this nomination can not take effect unless and until the United States Senate gives its Consent , as described in our Constitution , Article II , Section 2 .
label: case nmod obl punct det nsubj aux advmod root obj mark cc conj det amod compound nsubj advcl nmod obj punct mark advcl case nmod obl punct appos nummod punct appos nummod punct

text: A copy of the Constitution , with links back to the official source , is located at http://loveallpeople.org/usconstitutiona.txt

text: Judge Samuel Alito is very highly qualified by all of the normal standards used to evaluate candidates for this position :
label: compound nsubj flat cop advmod advmod root case obl case det amod nmod acl mark advcl obj case det nmod punct

text: He has a very high intellect .
label: nsubj root det advmod amod obj punct

text: He graduated very high in his class , from Princeton undergraduate and from Law School at Yale .
label: nsubj root advmod advmod case nmod obl punct case compound obl cc case compound conj case nmod punct

text: He has a long and distinguished record , including many years as a Federal Appeals Judge , the next level below Supreme Court .
label: nsubj root det amod cc conj obj punct case amod nmod case det amod compound nmod punct det amod appos case amod nmod punct

text: He has encyclopedic knowledge of hundreds of different Supreme Court cases , and he can recite details from memory .
label: nsubj root amod obj case nmod case amod amod compound nmod punct cc nsubj aux conj obj case obl punct

text: He demonstrates an excellent " Judicial Temperament , " being courteous , mild - mannered , respectful of all people ; careful in his work , meticulous in detail .
label: nsubj root det amod punct amod obj punct punct cop advcl punct amod punct conj punct conj case det obl punct conj case nmod obl punct conj case obl punct

text: His co-workers love him .
label: nmod nsubj root obj punct

text: His fellow judges love him .
label: nmod amod nsubj root obj punct

text: His family loves him .
label: nmod nsubj root obj punct

text: President Bush loves him .
label: nsubj flat root obj punct

text: Yes , it is true that some people do n't like the way they think he will vote on the Supreme Court .
label: discourse punct nsubj cop root mark det nsubj aux advmod ccomp det obj nsubj acl nsubj aux ccomp case det amod obl punct

text: But other people do like the way they think he will vote , and the ones who favor him seem to outnumber the ones who oppose him .
label: cc amod nsubj aux root det obj nsubj acl nsubj aux ccomp punct cc det nsubj nsubj acl obj conj mark xcomp det obj nsubj acl obj punct

text: So now the Senate is getting ready to vote soon , on whether to approve him or not ; and at this moment ( evening of Jan. 27 , 2006 ) it looks like he has more than the fifty - one votes needed for approval .
label: advmod advmod det nsubj aux root xcomp mark xcomp advmod punct mark mark mark advcl obj cc conj punct cc case det obl punct appos case nmod nummod punct nummod punct nsubj conj mark nsubj advcl obj case det compound punct nummod obl acl case obl punct

text: The President is very eager to go ahead quickly and get this vote , because he very much wants to have Samuel Alito on the Supreme Court , to be judging the cases Bush is interested in .
label: det nsubj cop advmod root mark xcomp advmod advmod cc conj det obj punct mark nsubj advmod advmod advcl mark xcomp obj flat case det amod obl punct mark aux advcl det obj nsubj cop acl obl punct

text: So there is a lot of hurry - up pressure on the Senate to give its prompt vote of approval .
label: advmod expl root det nsubj case compound punct compound nmod case det nmod mark acl nmod amod obj case nmod punct

text: There is an old saying that applies in this situation : " Act in haste , repent at leisure . "
label: expl root det amod nsubj nsubj acl case det obl punct punct parataxis case obl punct parataxis case obl punct punct

text: Sometimes you can make a bad decision very quickly , then regret it for many years to come .
label: advmod nsubj aux root det amod obj advmod advmod punct advmod parataxis obj case amod obl mark acl punct

text: That is what is about to happen with Judge Samuel Alito , in my opinion , because he has one tragic flaw - a very serious blind spot in his thinking - which makes him completely unacceptable for the position of Supreme Court Justice : He does not really agree with the system of " Checks and Balances " built into the Constitution , and he is ready to start tearing it down in order to follow the " Unitary Executive Theory , " which calls for vastly - increased Presidential Power at the expense of Congress and the Supreme Court .
label: nsubj cop root cop acl mark xcomp case compound obl flat punct case nmod obl punct mark nsubj advcl nummod amod obj punct det advmod amod amod appos case nmod nmod punct nsubj acl obj advmod xcomp case det obl case amod compound nmod punct nsubj aux advmod advmod parataxis case det obl case punct nmod cc conj punct acl case det obl punct cc nsubj cop conj mark xcomp xcomp obj compound mark fixed mark advcl det punct amod amod obj punct punct nsubj acl case advmod punct amod amod obl case det nmod case nmod cc det amod conj punct

text: And because of this tragic flaw . . .
label: cc case fixed det amod root punct punct punct

text: " He Would Tear Down Our System Of Checks And Balances , Giving Far Too Much Power To The President . "
label: punct nsubj aux root compound nmod obj case nmod cc conj punct advcl advmod advmod amod obj case det obl punct punct

text: In our Constitutional system , we have three branches of the Federal Government : the Legislative , Executive , and Judicial branches .
label: case nmod amod obl punct nsubj root nummod obj case det amod nmod punct det amod punct conj punct cc conj appos punct

text: And the basic idea behind the Checks and Balances we have is that if one branch of the Government goes crazy , the other two can hold it down .
label: cc det amod nsubj case det nmod cc conj nsubj acl cop mark mark nummod nsubj case det nmod advcl xcomp punct det amod nsubj aux root obj advmod punct

text: But Samuel Alito believes in a little - known Constitutional theory - called the " Unitary Executive Theory " - which says that the President should have complete control over the Executive Branch , and that the Executive Branch should be in charge of almost everything that the Government actually does , including the functions of the Independent Agencies which were designed to be free of Presidential control , and the Military , which exists , which is regulated , and which is funded by specific authority given by the Constitution to Congress , not to the President .
label: cc nsubj flat root case det compound punct amod amod obl punct acl det punct amod amod xcomp punct punct nsubj acl mark det nsubj aux ccomp amod obj case det amod nmod punct cc mark det amod nsubj aux cop case conj case advmod nmod obj det nsubj advmod acl punct case det nmod case det amod nmod nsubj aux acl mark cop advcl case amod obl punct cc det conj punct nsubj acl punct nsubj aux conj punct cc nsubj aux conj case amod obl acl case det obl case obl punct advmod case det nmod punct

text: The Military is not part of the Executive Branch : it is a separate entity .
label: det nsubj cop advmod root case det amod nmod punct nsubj cop det amod parataxis punct

text: " Commander In Chief " does n't mean that he is the boss of the Military , merely that he is the Administrator , just as he is the Administrator of the Executive Branch , charged with " executing faithfully " all the laws passed by Congress and all the Decisions rendered by the Supreme Court .
label: punct nsubj case nmod punct aux advmod root mark nsubj cop det ccomp case det nmod punct conj mark nsubj cop det orphan punct advmod mark nsubj cop det advcl case det amod nmod punct acl mark punct advcl advmod punct det det obj acl case obl cc det det conj acl case det amod obl punct

text: Under the Unitary Executive Theory , the Laws of Congress and Decisions of the Supreme Court have no actual authority unless the President agrees with them .
label: case det amod amod obl punct det nsubj case nmod cc conj case det amod nmod root det amod obj mark det nsubj advcl case obl punct

text: And so Congress and the Supreme Court become mere advisors to the President , with no real authority over him .
label: cc advmod nsubj cc det amod conj root amod xcomp case det nmod punct case det amod nmod case nmod punct

text: And the President becomes a Dictator , unrestrained by anything in the Constitution , backed up by the Armed Forces , which would be entirely under his personal control .
label: cc det nsubj root det xcomp punct amod case obl case det nmod punct acl compound case det amod obl punct nsubj aux cop advmod case nmod amod acl punct

text: And thus the United States of America - The Land Of The Free And The Home Of The Brave - becomes just another Military Dictatorship , no better than Nazi Germany or Fascist Italy during World War II .
label: cc advmod det amod nsubj case nmod punct det appos case det nmod cc det conj case det nmod punct root advmod det amod xcomp punct advmod amod case compound obl cc amod conj case compound nmod nummod punct

text: AND THAT IS WHY ALL AMERICANS SHOULD OPPOSE THE NOMINATION OF SAMUEL ALITO .

text: Ever since he ate up Red Riding Hood 's grandma and blew down the houses of two - thirds of the Three Little Pigs , the Big Bad Wolf has held a persistently bad reputation .
label: advmod mark nsubj advcl compound amod compound nmod case obj cc conj compound det obj case nummod punct nmod case det compound amod nmod punct det amod amod nsubj aux root det advmod amod obj punct

text: In part because of that reputation , the gray wolf was nearly exterminated from the lower 48 states by the 1920s , except for a small remnant population on Isle Royale National Park in Michigan 's Lake Superior .
label: case nmod case fixed det obl punct det amod nsubj aux advmod root case det amod nummod obl case det obl punct case case det amod compound obl case compound amod amod nmod case nmod case compound nmod punct

text: The last wolf was killed in Yellowstone National Park in 1943 .

text: Western sheep and cattle ranchers , on whose behalf this extermination campaign was conducted , gratefully dusted their hands of the wolf and wrote him off as a job well done .

text: Like UFOs or Sasquatch , several people claimed to see fleeting lone wolves , usually in Yellowstone .

text: If so , this happy band has not been heard from since .

text: Rumor also had it some renegade biologist brought a caged pair to Yellowstone and released them into the wild sometime in the 1970s , hoping to reestablish a breeding population .

text: Eventually , a trickle of support appeared for bringing the predator back to its former home range in the northern Rocky Mountains .

text: This trickle grew into a flood , resulting in 14 wolves being reintroduced in Yellowstone in 1995 by the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service -- albeit over the strong and still - continuing objections of ranchers .

text: One compelling argument for reintroduction was the wolf acts as a keystone predator , an animal that affects the populations , behavior and ecology of a wide variety of species within its range .

text: Some recent research conducted by Oregon State University has given considerable credence to this idea .

text: OSU forestry professors William Ripple and Robert Beschta have found that wolves actually promote stream - bank stabilization , although they have given the phenomenon the unfortunate name of " the ecology of fear " -- something that smacks of the horrible PR resulting from the wolf 's relationships with Riding Hood and the Three Pigs .

text: They explained that elk in Yellowstone used to browse unmolested on young aspen and willow growing near the banks of streams , a behavior that prevented the saplings from reaching mature stages and increased the possibility of soil erosion .

label: det nsubj nsubj acl mark cop xcomp case det compound obl cop advmod det root case nmod punct punct

text: This simple change has triggered a veritable ecological cascade in Yellowstone .

text: " It may be uninteresting to a lot of people , " Beschta told Blue Planet .

text: But we 've been looking at streamside communities .

text: Boulder , CO , Nov. 15 ( UPI ) --

text: Scientists can argue all they want about how many degrees Celsius -- or Fahrenheit -- the planet is warming and what the trend portends , but meanwhile Earth 's plants , insects and animals are not waiting for the outcome .
label: nsubj aux root obl nsubj acl mark advmod amod obl compound punct cc conj punct det nsubj aux advcl cc obj det nsubj conj punct cc advmod nmod case nsubj punct conj cc conj aux advmod conj case det obl punct

text: They already are altering their patterns of behavior in response to what is happening .
label: nsubj advmod aux root nmod obj case nmod case obl mark nsubj aux acl punct

text: It turns out one of the surest barometers of the warming climate is the response of the non-human natural world to changing conditions , and biologists who study the responses have been aware for some years the biosphere is acknowledging global warming .
label: nsubj root compound nsubj case det amod nmod case det amod nmod cop det ccomp case det amod amod nmod case amod nmod punct cc nsubj nsubj acl det obj aux cop conj case det obl det nsubj aux ccomp amod obj punct

text: Nina Leopold Bradley , a plant ecologist and daughter of the conservation pioneer Aldo Leopold , published a 1999 paper in the Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences on her 61 - year uninterrupted phenological records .
label: nsubj flat flat punct det compound appos cc conj case det compound nmod appos flat punct root det nummod obj case det obl case det amod nmod case nmod case nmod nummod punct compound amod amod obl punct

text: Phenology studies an organism 's development and life cycle -- the pulse of life .
label: nsubj root det nmod case obj cc compound conj punct det appos case nmod punct

text: Bradley 's record of 300 phenophases found that even prior to 1999 , spring was arriving in higher latitudes several weeks earlier than in the earlier years of her data .
label: nmod case nsubj case nummod nmod root mark advmod case fixed obl punct nsubj aux ccomp case amod obl amod obl advmod mark case det amod advcl case nmod nmod punct

text: Birds arrived sooner on their migrations from the south and plants flowered earlier .
label: nsubj root advmod case nmod obl case det nmod cc nsubj conj advmod punct

text: The Eastern phoebe is showing up about 20 days before it used to .
label: det amod nsubj aux root compound advmod nummod obl mark nsubj advcl xcomp punct

text: The forest phlox is blooming in late April instead of mid-May .

text: Half of the 300 phenophases Leopold tracked showed a response consistent with warming .
label: nsubj case det nummod nmod nsubj acl root det obj amod case obl punct

text: In England , the cuckoo returns earlier .
label: case obl punct det nsubj root advmod punct

text: An analysis of 65 bird species in the United Kingdom shows about one - third are laying their eggs four to seven days earlier than they did 25 years ago .

label: det amod compound nsubj aux root case nummod case nmod compound punct compound obl cc nummod compound conj punct acl advmod advmod nummod obj punct

text: Syria also possesses one of the largest arsenals of ballistic missiles in the region , comprised primarily of SCUD - derived systems .
label: nsubj advmod root obj case det amod nmod case amod nmod case det nmod punct acl advmod case obl punct amod obl punct

text: Iran , North Korea and China have been willing providers of state - of - the - art technologies .
label: nsubj punct compound conj cc conj aux cop amod root case compound punct case punct det punct nmod nmod punct

text: 4 . China and the US Economy
label: nummod punct root cc det compound conj

text: While the ominous possibilities of heightened Iraqi chaos , missiles in the Gulf , and Syrian involvement loom large if the US attacks Iran , all pale in comparison to the involvement of China in any US / Iran engagement .
label: mark det amod nsubj case amod amod nmod punct conj case det nmod punct cc amod conj advcl xcomp mark det nsubj advcl obj punct nsubj root case obl case det nmod case nmod case det compound punct compound nmod punct

text: China 's economy is exploding , hampered only by their great thirst for petroleum and natural gas to fuel their industry .
label: nmod case nsubj aux root punct advcl advmod case nmod amod obl case nmod cc amod conj mark acl nmod obj punct

text: In the last several months , China has inked deals with Iran for $ 70 billion dollars worth of Iranian oil and natural gas .
label: case det amod amod obl punct nsubj aux root obj case nmod case nmod compound nummod appos nmod case amod nmod cc amod conj punct

text: China will purchase 250 million tons of liquefied natural gas from Iran over the next 30 years , will develop the massive Yadavaran oil field in Iran , and will receive 150,000 barrels of oil per day from that field .
label: nsubj aux root compound nummod obj case amod amod nmod case obl case det amod nummod obl punct aux conj det amod compound compound obj case nmod punct cc aux conj nummod obj case nmod case obl case det obl punct

text: China is seeking the construction of a pipeline from Iran to the Caspian Sea , where it would link with another planned pipeline running from Kazakhstan to China .
label: nsubj aux root det obj case det nmod case nmod case det compound nmod punct advmod nsubj aux acl case det amod obl acl case obl case obl punct

text: Any US attack on Iran could be perceived by China as a direct threat to its economic health .
label: det compound nsubj case nmod aux aux root case obl case det amod obl case nmod amod nmod punct

text: Further , any fighting in the Persian Gulf would imperil the tankers running China 's liquefied natural gas through the Strait of Hormuz .
label: advmod punct det nsubj case det compound nmod aux root det obj acl nmod case amod amod obj case det obl case nmod punct

text: Should China decide to retaliate against the US to defend its oil and natural gas deal with Iran , the US would be faced with a significant threat .
label: aux nsubj advcl mark xcomp case det obl mark advcl nmod compound cc amod conj obj case nmod punct det nsubj aux aux root case det amod obl punct

text: This threat exists not merely on a military level , though China could force a confrontation in the Pacific by way of Taiwan .
label: det nsubj root advmod advmod case det amod obl punct mark nsubj aux advcl det obj case det nmod case obl case nmod punct

text: More significantly , China holds a large portion of the American economy in the palm of its hand .
label: advmod advmod punct nsubj root det amod obj case det amod nmod case det obl case nmod nmod punct

text: Paul Craig Roberts , writing for The American Conservative , said in July of 2005 that " As a result of many years of persistent trade surpluses with the United States , the Japanese government holds dollar reserves of approximately $ 1 trillion .
label: nsubj flat flat punct advcl case det amod obl punct root case obl case nmod mark punct case det obl case amod nmod case amod compound nmod case det amod nmod punct det amod nsubj ccomp compound obj case advmod nmod compound nummod punct

text: China 's accumulation of dollars is approximately $ 600 billion .
label: nmod case nsubj case nmod cop advmod root compound nummod punct

text: South Korea holds about $ 200 billion .
label: compound nsubj root advmod obj compound nummod punct

text: These sums give these countries enormous leverage over the United States .
label: det nsubj root det iobj amod obj case det amod nmod punct

text: By dumping some portion of their reserves , these countries could put the dollar under intense pressure and send U.S. interest rates skyrocketing .
label: mark advcl det obj case nmod nmod punct det nsubj aux root det obj case amod obl cc conj compound compound obj xcomp punct

text: Washington would really have to anger Japan and Korea to provoke such action , but in a showdown with China - over Taiwan , for example - China holds the cards .
label: nsubj aux advmod root mark xcomp obj cc conj mark advcl amod obj punct cc case det obl case nmod punct case nmod punct case nmod punct nsubj conj det obj punct

text: China and Japan , and the world at large , have more dollar reserves than they require .
label: nsubj cc conj punct cc det conj case nmod punct root amod compound obj mark nsubj advcl punct

text: They would have no problem teaching a hegemonic superpower a lesson if the need arose . "
label: nsubj aux root det obj xcomp det amod iobj det obj mark det nsubj advcl punct punct

text: " The hardest blow on Americans , " concluded Roberts , " will fall when China does revalue its currency .
label: punct det amod nsubj case nmod punct punct parataxis nsubj punct punct aux root advmod nsubj aux advcl nmod obj punct

text: When China 's currency ceases to be undervalued , American shoppers in Wal - Mart , where 70 percent of the goods on the shelves are made in China , will think they are in Neiman Marcus .
label: advmod nmod case nsubj advcl mark aux xcomp punct amod nsubj case compound punct nmod punct advmod nummod nsubj case det nmod case det nmod aux acl case obl punct aux root nsubj cop case compound ccomp punct

text: Price increases will cause a dramatic reduction in American real incomes .
label: compound nsubj aux root det amod obj case amod amod nmod punct

text: If this coincides with rising interest rates and a setback in the housing market , American consumers will experience the hardest times since the Great Depression . "
label: mark nsubj advcl case amod compound obl cc det conj case det compound nmod punct amod nsubj aux root det amod obj case det amod nmod punct punct

text: In short , China has the American economy by the throat .
label: case obl punct nsubj root det amod obj case det obl punct

text: Should they decide to squeeze , we will all feel it .
label: aux nsubj advcl mark xcomp punct nsubj aux advmod root obj punct

text: China 's strong hand in this even extends to the diplomatic realm ; China is a permanent member of the United Nations Security Council , and could veto any actions against Iran proposed by the United States .

text: 5 . American Preparedness
label: nummod punct amod root

text: American citizens have for decades taken it as a given that our military can overwhelm and overcome any foe on the battlefield .
label: amod nsubj aux case obl root expl case det obl mark nmod nsubj aux ccomp cc conj det obj case det obl punct

text: The rapid victory during the first Gulf War cemented this perception .
label: det amod nsubj case det amod compound nmod root det obj punct

text: The last three years of the Iraq occupation , however , have sapped this confidence .
label: det amod nummod nsubj case det compound nmod punct advmod punct aux root det obj punct

text: Worse , the occupation has done great damage to the strength of the American military , justifying the decrease in confidence .
label: advmod punct det nsubj aux root amod obj case det obl case det amod nmod punct advcl det obj case nmod punct

text: Thanks to repeated deployments to Iraq and Afghanistan , recruiting is at an all - time low .
label: obl case amod nmod case nmod cc conj punct nsubj root case det det punct compound obl punct

text: Soldiers with vital training and know - how are refusing to re-enlist .
label: nsubj case amod nmod cc compound punct conj aux root mark xcomp punct

text: Across the board , the American military is stretched to the breaking point .
label: case det obl punct det amod nsubj aux root case det compound obl punct

text: Two vaunted economists - one a Nobel Prize winner and the other a nationally renowned budget expert - have analyzed the data at hand and put a price tag on the Iraq occupation .
label: nummod amod nsubj punct nsubj det compound compound appos cc det nsubj det advmod amod compound conj punct aux root det obj case nmod cc conj det compound obj case det compound obl punct

text: According to Linda Bilmes of Harvard and Nobel Laureate Joseph E. Stiglitz of Columbia University , the final cost of the Iraq occupation will run between $ 1 trillion and $ 2 trillion , surpassing by orders of magnitude the estimates put forth by the Bush administration .
label: case fixed obl flat case nmod cc compound compound conj flat flat case compound nmod punct det amod nsubj case det compound nmod aux root case obl compound nummod cc conj compound nummod punct advcl case obl case nmod det obj acl advmod case det obl flat punct

text: If an engagement with Iran envelops our forces in Iraq , and comes to involve Syria , our economy will likely shatter under the strain of fighting so many countries simultaneously .
label: mark det nsubj case nmod advcl nmod obj case nmod punct cc conj mark xcomp obj punct nmod nsubj aux advmod root case det obl mark acl advmod amod obj advmod punct

text: Add to this the economic threat posed by China , and the economic threat implicit in any substantial disruption of the distribution of Mideast petroleum to the globe .
label: root case obl det amod obj acl case obl punct cc det amod conj amod case det amod obl case det nmod case compound nmod case det nmod punct

text: If Iran and Syria - with their significant armaments , missile technologies and suspected chemical weapons capabilities - decide to engage with the relatively undersized US force in Iraq , our troops there will be fish in a barrel .
label: mark nsubj cc conj punct case nmod amod nmod punct compound conj cc amod amod compound conj punct advcl mark xcomp case det advmod amod compound obl case nmod punct nmod nsubj advmod aux cop root case det nmod punct

text: Iran 's position over the Gulf would make resupply by ship and air support from carriers a dangerous affair .
label: nmod case nsubj case det nmod aux root obj case nmod cc compound conj case nmod det amod xcomp punct

text: In the worst - case scenario , the newly - minted American order of battle requiring the use of nuclear weapons to rescue a surrounded and imperiled force could come into play , hurling the entire planet into military and diplomatic bedlam .
label: case det amod punct compound obl punct det advmod punct amod amod nsubj case nmod acl det obj case amod nmod mark acl det amod cc conj obj aux root case obl punct advcl det amod obj case amod cc conj obl punct

text: Conclusion : Is Any of This Possible ?
label: root punct cop nsubj case nmod appos punct

text: The question must be put as directly as possible : what manner of maniac would undertake a path so fraught with peril and potential economic catastrophe ?
label: det nsubj aux aux root advmod advmod mark advcl punct det nsubj case nmod aux ccomp det obj advmod amod case obl cc amod amod conj punct

text: It is difficult to imagine a justification for any action that could envelop the United States in a military and economic conflict with Iraq , Iran , Syria and China simultaneously .
label: expl cop root mark csubj det obj case det nmod nsubj aux acl det amod obj case det amod cc conj obl case nmod punct conj punct conj cc conj advmod punct

text: Iran is suspected by many nations of working towards the development of nuclear weapons , but even this justification has been tossed into a cocked hat .
label: nsubj aux root case amod obl mark advcl case det obl case amod nmod punct cc advmod det nsubj aux aux conj case det amod obl punct

text: Recently , Russian president Vladimir Putin bluntly stated that Iran is not developing its nuclear capability for any reasons beyond peaceful energy creation , and pledged to continue assisting Iran in this endeavor .
label: advmod punct amod compound nsubj flat advmod root mark nsubj aux advmod ccomp nmod amod obj case det obl case amod compound nmod punct cc conj mark xcomp xcomp obj case det obl punct

text: Therefore , any attack upon Iran 's nuclear facilities will bring Russia into the mess .
label: advmod punct det nsubj case nmod case amod nmod aux root obj case det obl punct

text: Iran also stands accused of aiding terrorism across the globe .
label: nsubj advmod root advcl mark advcl obj case det obl punct

text: The dangers implicit in any attack upon that nation , however , seem to significantly offset whatever gains could be made in the so - called " War on Terror . "
label: det nsubj amod case det obl case det nmod punct advmod punct root mark advmod xcomp det obj aux aux acl case det advmod punct amod punct obl case nmod punct punct

text: Unfortunately , all the dangers in the world are no match for the self - assurance of a bubble - encased zealot .
label: advmod punct det det nsubj case det nmod cop det root case det compound punct nmod case det obl punct amod nmod punct

text: What manner of maniac would undertake such a dangerous course ?
label: det nsubj case nmod aux root det det amod obj punct

text: George W. Bush and his administration have consistently undertaken incredibly dangerous courses of action in order to garner political power on the home front .
label: nsubj flat flat cc nmod conj aux advmod root advmod amod obj case nmod mark fixed mark advcl amod obj case det compound obl punct

text: Recall the multiple terror threats lobbed out by the administration whenever damaging political news appeared in the media .

text: More significantly , recall Iraq .
